next
  Summary: Inventory Balance, equipped-ammo coverage, DLTX ceilings, Smart Balance rename
  Added:
    Added: Inventory Balance. Long-lived stalkers (companions, story NPCs, gulag survivors) no longer hoard items across hundreds of game-days.
    Added: Periodic scan trims online stalkers in small batches, at most once per game-day per NPC.
    Added: configs/alifebalance/ab_inventory_policy.ltx. DLTX-overridable per-category ceilings. Replaces hardcoded CULL_POLICY table.
    Added: Shared LTX shape with ap_trade_policy.ltx and ap_stash_policy.ltx via xinventory.load_policy.
    Added: Explicit entries for ammo_slot_2_t1, ammo_slot_2_t2, ammo_slot_3_t1, ammo_slot_3_t2. Equipped-rifle ammo bounded.
    Added: Untouchables filtered centrally by xinventory.get_category. Quest, equipped, story_id, companion-gifted, and player-strapped items never released.
    Added: Traders skipped at the scheduler level via xcreature.is_unscriptable.
    Added: MCM Inventory Balance tab. Defaults: enabled, 1 NPC per frame, 20 per cycle, 24 game-hour rescan cooldown.
  Changed:
    Changed: MCM reorganized into separate Smart Balance and Inventory Balance tabs (was a single General tab). Existing MCM settings reset to defaults on upgrade.
    Changed: Smart Balance death counter credits every non-vermin death (was filtered via xsquad.is_protected to exclude protected NPCs).
    Changed: Smart Pacing renamed to Smart Balance. Label only, no behavior change.
  Compatibility:
    Requires NPC corpse looting enabled. Disable "311- NPC Stop Looting Dead Bodies - DTTheGunslinger" or any equivalent.

1.0.2
  Summary: Crash fix on xlibs 1.7.0
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing on xlibs 1.7.0 at ab_recipe.script:141. Adopt renamed xsmart.find_smarts_spawning (was xsmart.find_smarts_with_recipe pre-1.7.0). Requires xlibs 1.7.0+.

1.0.1
  Summary: Crash fix on malformed respawn params, third-party respawn-delay compatibility
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing budget evaluation when scanning malformed or misconfigured smart terrains whose respawn_params.num condlist has no default branch.
  Compatibility:
    Skip smart terrains whose last_respawn_update is set to a future game-time by another mod. Honors third-party deferred-respawn intent instead of overriding it.

1.0.0
  First release. Advances respawn cooldowns at smart terrains where combat has produced deaths, so active regions recover faster without affecting the rest of the map.
